Program: Discovery
Title: Russell Foster
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01jq26t
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 27 Oct 2013
Russell Foster, professor of circadian neuroscience at Oxford University, is obsessed with biological clocks. He talks to Jim al-Khalili about how light controls our wellbeing from jet lag to serious mental health problems. Professor Foster explains how he moved from being a poor student at school to the scientist who discovered a new way in which animals detect light. Image: Russell Foster Copyright: BBC Show less